WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.680 --> 00:00:03.970
&gt;&gt; From the Library of
Congress in Washington, DC.

00:00:23.350 --> 00:00:25.310
&gt;&gt; Pam Jackson: So, I'm
Pam Jackson, I'm director

00:00:25.310 --> 00:00:28.500
for the Center for the Book
here at the Library of Congress.

00:00:28.500 --> 00:00:32.710
We are part of the library's
newly created national

00:00:32.710 --> 00:00:35.660
and international outreach
unit and I welcome you

00:00:35.660 --> 00:00:38.300
and thank you for being here.

00:00:38.300 --> 00:00:41.360
To our partners and colleagues
cosponsoring today's events,

00:00:41.360 --> 00:00:45.010
to the program participants and
to our speakers, to collectors,

00:00:45.010 --> 00:00:47.260
to friends, to each of
you tonight thank you

00:00:47.260 --> 00:00:50.330
for joining us, thank you
for giving us your attention

00:00:50.330 --> 00:00:52.830
and being generous with us.

00:00:52.830 --> 00:00:56.780
The library's central mission is
to provide the American people

00:00:56.780 --> 00:01:00.370
with a rich, diverse,
enduring source of knowledge,

00:01:00.370 --> 00:01:04.690
one that can be relied
upon to inform and inspire

00:01:04.690 --> 00:01:07.650
and engage people to
support their intellectual

00:01:07.650 --> 00:01:09.840
and creative endeavors.

00:01:09.840 --> 00:01:12.810
And a part of our vision
here at the library is

00:01:12.810 --> 00:01:16.980
that we are the chief steward
of the record of knowledge

00:01:16.980 --> 00:01:19.180
for America and thus the world,

00:01:19.180 --> 00:01:21.590
creating a springboard
to the future.

00:01:21.590 --> 00:01:25.440
It's a future that I hope to be
one of compassion and courage

00:01:25.440 --> 00:01:29.890
and industry and excitement
and remarkable accomplishment

00:01:29.890 --> 00:01:34.460
and achievement, and one of
tolerance and acceptance.

00:01:34.460 --> 00:01:37.770
And so, today's collectors
in their own rights are part

00:01:37.770 --> 00:01:44.230
of our goal and hope and
desire for stewards of records

00:01:44.230 --> 00:01:47.630
of knowledge and I applaud
you in your commitment

00:01:47.630 --> 00:01:49.490
and you celebrate
the accomplishments

00:01:49.490 --> 00:01:51.590
that will be shared tonight.

00:01:51.590 --> 00:01:54.830
Here, at the Center for the
Book, which includes the Poetry

00:01:54.830 --> 00:01:58.110
and Literature Center and the
Young Readers Center we promote

00:01:58.110 --> 00:02:02.110
books and libraries,
literacy and reading,

00:02:02.110 --> 00:02:05.460
poetry and literature because
we believe beyond a shadow

00:02:05.460 --> 00:02:10.510
of a doubt is the best way to
empowerment, to enlightenment,

00:02:10.510 --> 00:02:15.520
to educate and inform societies,
to protect and uphold democracy.

00:02:15.520 --> 00:02:18.480
We believe more than
anything else books

00:02:18.480 --> 00:02:22.170
and reading are the best
weapons against ignorance

00:02:22.170 --> 00:02:27.090
and intolerance and we thank you
for being part of our mission

00:02:27.090 --> 00:02:31.230
of service and fulfilling on
the promotion of knowledge

00:02:31.230 --> 00:02:35.130
and the inspiration
that books bring us.

00:02:35.130 --> 00:02:39.260
It's my job and my honor to
introduce our next speaker

00:02:39.260 --> 00:02:43.830
in the program John
Cole, John Y. Cole.

00:02:43.830 --> 00:02:46.470
Historian of the
Library of Congress,

00:02:46.470 --> 00:02:50.010
more importantly the founding
director of the Center

00:02:50.010 --> 00:02:53.100
for the Book which is
celebrating its 40th year

00:02:53.100 --> 00:02:55.090
in existence next year.

00:02:55.090 --> 00:02:58.470
With just the deepest gratitude
John for you and your role here

00:02:58.470 --> 00:03:02.190
at the library what you've
created and what's to come,

00:03:02.190 --> 00:03:04.190
thank you for creating
this event tonight

00:03:04.190 --> 00:03:06.450
and for leading us
the way forward.

00:03:06.450 --> 00:03:08.250
Welcome John Y. Cole.

00:03:08.250 --> 00:03:17.050
[ Applause ]

00:03:17.050 --> 00:03:18.350
&gt;&gt; John Cole: Thank you Pam.

00:03:18.350 --> 00:03:21.070
As you can see, I'm still
easing my way out of the Center

00:03:21.070 --> 00:03:24.690
for the Book, but very
excited about being the Library

00:03:24.690 --> 00:03:26.950
of Congress' first historian.

00:03:26.950 --> 00:03:29.960
And one of the things I
can record is the success

00:03:29.960 --> 00:03:34.350
of a program such as this one
of which has been transferred

00:03:34.350 --> 00:03:38.430
to the Library of
Congress in recent times.

00:03:38.430 --> 00:03:42.370
I want to say just a quick
word about this awards program.

00:03:42.370 --> 00:03:45.270
In 2005, the magazine Fine Books

00:03:45.270 --> 00:03:50.590
and Collections started this
program and competition to honor

00:03:50.590 --> 00:03:53.760
and to award student
book collectors

00:03:53.760 --> 00:03:58.790
and they went along very
well, but eventually some

00:03:58.790 --> 00:04:01.800
of the other people in the
book world, including people

00:04:01.800 --> 00:04:05.730
who are eager to become involved
agreed that we would take

00:04:05.730 --> 00:04:08.840
over in a new partnership
the sponsorship

00:04:08.840 --> 00:04:12.560
of the awards program for
certain here at the Library

00:04:12.560 --> 00:04:16.560
of Congress, but also with other
partners the administration

00:04:16.560 --> 00:04:17.860
of the program.

00:04:17.860 --> 00:04:21.680
And our purpose always has been
to kind of broaden the reach

00:04:21.680 --> 00:04:24.000
and to get more schools
and more students

00:04:24.000 --> 00:04:26.570
and more people involved
in book collecting.

00:04:26.570 --> 00:04:30.860
The purpose really is to
honor young collectors

00:04:30.860 --> 00:04:34.210
which we're doing tonight
and kind of push them gently

00:04:34.210 --> 00:04:38.070
and maybe not so gently into
becoming lifetime book lovers

00:04:38.070 --> 00:04:41.650
and accomplished collectors
and even bibliophiles

00:04:41.650 --> 00:04:43.130
if they aren't careful.

00:04:43.130 --> 00:04:45.420
So that's one of the ways

00:04:45.420 --> 00:04:47.940
that we are bringing
several groups together

00:04:47.940 --> 00:04:49.830
for the sponsorship of this.

00:04:49.830 --> 00:04:51.950
If you look at your program

00:04:51.950 --> 00:04:54.500
which you may have missed
the other sponsors are the

00:04:54.500 --> 00:04:57.820
Antiquarian Booksellers
Association of America,

00:04:57.820 --> 00:05:00.290
the Rare Book and Special
Collections Division

00:05:00.290 --> 00:05:03.300
of the Library of
Congress, the Fellowship

00:05:03.300 --> 00:05:07.220
of American Bibliophilic
Societies, and the Grolier Club

00:05:07.220 --> 00:05:10.230
and we are very grateful
to all of them and also

00:05:10.230 --> 00:05:12.190
to the contributors
and supporters

00:05:12.190 --> 00:05:15.050
and friends who've made
financial contributions

00:05:15.050 --> 00:05:17.540
at various levels
to this program.

00:05:17.540 --> 00:05:22.220
We hope that you like it, we
hope you continue to support it

00:05:22.220 --> 00:05:24.160
and we promise that
we will continue

00:05:24.160 --> 00:05:26.300
to bring you very
high-quality winners

00:05:26.300 --> 00:05:28.370
which we are doing tonight

00:05:28.370 --> 00:05:31.900
and I think you will enjoy
meeting them and learning

00:05:31.900 --> 00:05:37.800
about what they are able to
think about as collectors,

00:05:37.800 --> 00:05:40.040
it's really quite amazing.

00:05:40.040 --> 00:05:42.640
I would like to welcome
the Grolier Club

00:05:42.640 --> 00:05:46.880
as our latest partner
in this partnership

00:05:46.880 --> 00:05:49.390
and president Scott Clemons
is here and Scott would

00:05:49.390 --> 00:05:50.690
like to say a few words.

00:05:50.690 --> 00:05:53.570
Scott. There you are.

00:05:53.570 --> 00:05:55.870
&gt;&gt; Scott Clemons: Here I am.

00:05:59.300 --> 00:06:00.600
Thank you, John.

00:06:00.600 --> 00:06:01.900
I just -- the Grolier Club,

00:06:01.900 --> 00:06:03.290
how many of you know
of the Grolier Club?

00:06:03.290 --> 00:06:05.530
Oh, this warms my
heart to see this,

00:06:05.530 --> 00:06:07.770
thank you that makes
my day to see that.

00:06:07.770 --> 00:06:11.050
The Grolier Club was founded
in 1884 originally as a club

00:06:11.050 --> 00:06:13.520
for private collectors of books

00:06:13.520 --> 00:06:15.710
and since then it's
broadened a great deal

00:06:15.710 --> 00:06:17.440
to include institutional
collectors as well.

00:06:17.440 --> 00:06:19.400
Anyone tangibly involved
in the book arts,

00:06:19.400 --> 00:06:21.480
so there are bookmakers,
there are typographers,

00:06:21.480 --> 00:06:23.100
there are still a healthy dose

00:06:23.100 --> 00:06:25.590
of private collectors
such as myself.

00:06:25.590 --> 00:06:29.600
So, as sponsors of this award
it just makes all the sense

00:06:29.600 --> 00:06:32.070
in the world for the club
to meet collectors early on

00:06:32.070 --> 00:06:35.450
and introduce them to the
resources the club has to offer,

00:06:35.450 --> 00:06:40.760
most of which are people who
have been in this passion for 10

00:06:40.760 --> 00:06:45.360
or 30 or 50 or 60 or
more years as collectors.

00:06:45.360 --> 00:06:46.910
So, one of the things
that we did last year

00:06:46.910 --> 00:06:49.310
and that we're doing again this
year is that we are to each

00:06:49.310 --> 00:06:51.610
of the four honorees
offering a year's membership

00:06:51.610 --> 00:06:54.820
in the Grolier Club with all the
rights thereunto appertaining

00:06:54.820 --> 00:06:56.500
as the lawyers would say.

00:06:56.500 --> 00:06:59.070
And we hope to see
those people at the club

00:06:59.070 --> 00:07:00.930
and the various events
that the club does,

00:07:00.930 --> 00:07:02.760
including quite a
few here in DC.

00:07:02.760 --> 00:07:05.540
There are number of club
members in the greater DC area.

00:07:05.540 --> 00:07:10.460
We do three or four events a
year here in DC and nationwide,

00:07:10.460 --> 00:07:13.030
and increasingly even
worldwide as well.

00:07:13.030 --> 00:07:15.240
And as a matter fact I would
invite all of you to come

00:07:15.240 --> 00:07:17.740
to the Grolier Club in spite
of being a private club

00:07:17.740 --> 00:07:21.010
on 60th Street in
Manhattan it is also open

00:07:21.010 --> 00:07:23.990
to the public six days
a week with exhibitions

00:07:23.990 --> 00:07:25.600
and two different galleries,

00:07:25.600 --> 00:07:29.890
public lecture series,
a research library.

00:07:29.890 --> 00:07:32.420
So, stop by and when
you do ask for me

00:07:32.420 --> 00:07:34.540
and if I'm there I'll
say hello to you.

00:07:34.540 --> 00:07:37.320
So, thank you again for
letting us be a part of this

00:07:37.320 --> 00:07:38.670
and it's a privilege for
us to be a part of this

00:07:38.670 --> 00:07:39.970
and thank you John as well.

00:07:39.970 --> 00:07:44.480
&gt;&gt; John Cole: Thank you.

00:07:44.480 --> 00:07:45.780
Thank you.

00:07:45.780 --> 00:07:47.080
&gt;&gt; Scott Clemons: Thanks.

00:07:47.080 --> 00:07:48.380
&gt;&gt; John Cole: And tonight,

