00:16:21.350 --> 00:16:24.590
It was and sounds like it
must've been an unprecedented

00:16:24.590 --> 00:16:26.390
three-day meeting.

00:16:26.390 --> 00:16:31.040
Among her other activities
and honors Toni is the author

00:16:31.040 --> 00:16:34.750
of the Jemima Code,
two centuries

00:16:34.750 --> 00:16:38.550
of African-American
cookbooks published last year

00:16:38.550 --> 00:16:40.190
by the University
of Texas Press.

00:16:40.190 --> 00:16:44.620
It's an award-winning
bibliography and too late

00:16:44.620 --> 00:16:46.660
for this listing,
but with the cards

00:16:46.660 --> 00:16:48.490
from the winter here
are a couple

00:16:48.490 --> 00:16:51.940
of other acknowledgments
of this book.

00:16:51.940 --> 00:16:56.700
Here's one of the reviews, the
New York Times book review,

00:16:56.700 --> 00:17:00.620
Jemima code is no ordinary
book, it's a heaping helping,

00:17:00.620 --> 00:17:03.180
a long-overdue acknowledgment.

00:17:03.180 --> 00:17:08.790
From NPR's Best Books of 2005,
