00:51:51.290 --> 00:51:58.180
So, I grew up in a Zionist
Jewish youth movement called

00:51:58.180 --> 00:52:00.780
Habonim Dror, which is one

00:52:00.780 --> 00:52:04.210
of the first Zionist youth
movements that emerged

00:52:04.210 --> 00:52:06.880
after the Jewish
enlightenment in Europe

00:52:06.880 --> 00:52:10.680
which is called the Haskalah and
it was the move from orthodoxy

00:52:10.680 --> 00:52:14.080
to secularism that occurred.

00:52:14.080 --> 00:52:18.170
When Jews realized that
they didn't need to stay

00:52:18.170 --> 00:52:21.690
in the shtetl and that they
could be something more

00:52:21.690 --> 00:52:23.290
than that.

00:52:23.290 --> 00:52:29.370
And famously Habonim Dror was
the movement that produced two

00:52:29.370 --> 00:52:34.510
of the leaders of the
Warsaw ghetto uprising.

00:52:34.510 --> 00:52:39.300
And two years ago, I went to
Poland with my youth movement

00:52:39.300 --> 00:52:43.320
and we visited the site of
the Warsaw ghetto uprising,

00:52:43.320 --> 00:52:46.760
one of the sites, the final
resting place so to say

00:52:46.760 --> 00:52:53.250
and I felt very connected
with it.

00:52:53.250 --> 00:52:58.800
So, all my life I felt like I'm
a Jewish person who's not very

00:52:58.800 --> 00:53:02.040
observant but is very
connected spiritually

00:53:02.040 --> 00:53:04.280
to Jewish history
and Jewish culture.

00:53:04.280 --> 00:53:07.330
And you know that distinction
was hard for me to accept

00:53:07.330 --> 00:53:09.410
because you know when you go
to Jewish day school they sort

00:53:09.410 --> 00:53:15.110
