Judaism is through the Torah

00:53:15.110 --> 00:53:17.540
and didn't I feel
that and this was it

00:53:17.540 --> 00:53:19.920
and more specifically
it was Jewish women.

00:53:19.920 --> 00:53:25.630
And Jewish women who were
artists and poets and thinkers

00:53:25.630 --> 00:53:29.370
and who are more than
just Jewish women.

00:53:29.370 --> 00:53:33.270
And you know that's where the
collection really started,

00:53:33.270 --> 00:53:35.770
it started with some really
important Jewish women

00:53:35.770 --> 00:53:37.690
and their names are
Hannah Szenes

00:53:37.690 --> 00:53:41.780
who is an Israeli paratrooper
and poet and Zivia Lubetkin

00:53:41.780 --> 00:53:46.130
who was the leader of the Warsaw
ghetto uprising and so many more

00:53:46.130 --> 00:53:51.340
who tell these amazing stories
about Jewish resistance,

00:53:51.340 --> 00:53:55.200
which is the idea that there
will be life after this.

00:53:55.200 --> 00:53:58.140
And that is really what I wanted
to bring to the collection,

00:53:58.140 --> 00:54:02.030
that there will be life for
Jewish people after this.

